And this is hard, but
that is one of the keys

00:24:04.010 --> 00:24:06.240
to help make you a
more expanded person.

00:24:06.240 --> 00:24:09.960
Now I was really a
shy person as a kid.

00:24:09.960 --> 00:24:13.150
I was so shy that by
the time I was 17,

00:24:13.150 --> 00:24:16.790
I never actually had asked
a woman out on a date.

00:24:16.790 --> 00:24:19.760
But it is possible to learn to
overcome your fears relatively

00:24:19.760 --> 00:24:20.660
quickly.

00:24:20.660 --> 00:24:22.410
So what I did was
I said, I'm going

00:24:22.410 --> 00:24:26.960
to get rejected by 10 women
in one day, and if I do that,

00:24:26.960 --> 00:24:30.650
I will treat myself
to a trip to Hawaii.

00:24:30.650 --> 00:24:32.480
So I went to the
university bookstore

00:24:32.480 --> 00:24:34.840
and I go up to a woman.

00:24:34.840 --> 00:24:38.410
And I'm literally drenched
in sweat-- beads of sweat

00:24:38.410 --> 00:24:39.570
dripping down my face.

00:24:39.570 --> 00:24:46.260
I'm shaking, and I go up to
a woman, and I go, hello.

00:24:46.260 --> 00:24:48.990
This poor girl, she
looks at me and she says,

00:24:48.990 --> 00:24:49.740
are you all right?

00:24:49.740 --> 00:24:52.800
Do you need an ambulance?

00:24:52.800 --> 00:24:55.900
She thought I was having
some kind of seizure.

00:24:55.900 --> 00:24:58.720
I said, no, don't
call an ambulance.

00:24:58.720 --> 00:25:00.990
So obviously, an awkward
conversation ensued,

00:25:00.990 --> 00:25:03.710
and I asked her out and she
said, no, I have a boyfriend,

00:25:03.710 --> 00:25:04.780
but thank you for asking.

00:25:04.780 --> 00:25:06.630
I really appreciate that.

00:25:06.630 --> 00:25:07.440
Are sure you're OK?

00:25:07.440 --> 00:25:07.940
Yeah.

00:25:11.130 --> 00:25:12.790
One down, nine more to go.

00:25:12.790 --> 00:25:16.050
And when you face your fears,
it gets easier and easier

00:25:16.050 --> 00:25:16.840
with each person.

00:25:16.840 --> 00:25:19.280
So by the fourth woman,
I'm feeling like, wow, I'm

00:25:19.280 --> 00:25:20.660
breaking through
a lifelong fear.

00:25:20.660 --> 00:25:22.610
This feels great.

00:25:22.610 --> 00:25:25.020
I could do this
every Friday night.

00:25:25.020 --> 00:25:27.040
So I'm going through this,
but the seventh woman

00:25:27.040 --> 00:25:28.270
ruined my momentum.

00:25:28.270 --> 00:25:31.720
By now, I kind of had a
script, I knew how it would go.

00:25:31.720 --> 00:25:33.060
So I say, hey, I'm new here.

00:25:33.060 --> 00:25:34.230
I haven't met many people.

00:25:34.230 --> 00:25:35.620
You look very nice.

00:25:35.620 --> 00:25:37.990
Would you be interested
in going out some time?

00:25:37.990 --> 00:25:42.340
And she said, sure.

00:25:42.340 --> 00:25:46.880
It was at that moment I realized
I had no script for "sure."

00:25:46.880 --> 00:25:48.740
So I said, sure what?

00:25:48.740 --> 00:25:50.830
She said, I'd love
to go out with you.

00:25:50.830 --> 00:25:51.350
Really?

00:25:51.350 --> 00:25:51.850
OK.

00:25:51.850 --> 00:25:52.850
I wrote down her number.

00:25:52.850 --> 00:25:53.630
Great.

00:25:53.630 --> 00:25:55.840
Now I feel really happy.

00:25:55.840 --> 00:25:58.930
And when you are
happy, it kind of

00:25:58.930 --> 00:26:01.310
is like a magnet towards you.

00:26:01.310 --> 00:26:04.080
So the next woman said
yes, and the next,

00:26:04.080 --> 00:26:07.630
and the next, and the next,
and the next, and the next,

00:26:07.630 --> 00:26:08.680
and the next.

00:26:08.680 --> 00:26:11.000
I had eight straight dates.

