00:26:42.980 --> 00:26:44.737
she wanted to get to know.

00:26:44.737 --> 00:26:45.570
So that didn't work.

00:26:45.570 --> 00:26:47.260
But I threw on some water.

00:26:47.260 --> 00:26:48.660
I did my shaking routine.

00:26:48.660 --> 00:26:50.080
I got my three final rejections.

00:26:50.080 --> 00:26:53.900
I went to Hawaii,
but most important, I

00:26:53.900 --> 00:26:58.750
learned that facing your
fear is a learnable skill

00:26:58.750 --> 00:27:03.020
and that you can overcome
lifelong fears in an hour.

00:27:03.020 --> 00:27:05.810
People ask me, how did I meet
Mother Teresa, the Dalai Lama,

00:27:05.810 --> 00:27:07.190
Deepak Chopra, all these people?

00:27:07.190 --> 00:27:10.130
I said, well, when I have 17,
I faced my fear of rejection.

00:27:10.130 --> 00:27:13.560
I took it from a 10
to a 5 in one hour,

00:27:13.560 --> 00:27:16.070
and that changed my life.

00:27:16.070 --> 00:27:18.480
So being willing to
do that is really key.

00:27:18.480 --> 00:27:20.600
Fear of embarrassment,
fear of failure,

00:27:20.600 --> 00:27:24.100
fear of rejection--
the big three.

00:27:24.100 --> 00:27:26.210
Just out of curiosity--
probably a lot you

00:27:26.210 --> 00:27:30.100
saw the movie "The Matrix"
in which Neo is asked,

00:27:30.100 --> 00:27:34.240
do you want a red pill,
which involves seeing

00:27:34.240 --> 00:27:37.920
the truth about yourself
and facing fear;

00:27:37.920 --> 00:27:39.990
or do you want the
blue pill, which

00:27:39.990 --> 00:27:44.827
involves being lulled to sleep,
believing whatever you want?

00:27:44.827 --> 00:27:46.660
Just out of a show of
hands, how many of you

00:27:46.660 --> 00:27:50.380
Googlers would say
that, given that choice,

00:27:50.380 --> 00:27:53.719
that you would have
chosen the red pill?

00:27:53.719 --> 00:27:55.510
Raise your hand if
you're in that category.

00:27:55.510 --> 00:27:57.720
OK, good.

00:27:57.720 --> 00:28:00.116
Now many think you would
have taken the blue bill?

00:28:00.116 --> 00:28:00.616
None?

00:28:00.616 --> 00:28:01.900
Wow.

00:28:01.900 --> 00:28:03.040
That's impressive.

00:28:03.040 --> 00:28:05.900
Must be a pretty fearless group.

00:28:05.900 --> 00:28:07.010
That's good to know.

00:28:07.010 --> 00:28:08.060
OK.

00:28:08.060 --> 00:28:11.260
It's important to know that
because that decision--

00:28:11.260 --> 00:28:13.950
whether you're a red or a
blue pill taker-- really

00:28:13.950 --> 00:28:16.995
determines the course of your
life to a very large extent.

00:28:19.500 --> 00:28:21.700
Seventh key to knowing
how to be happy

00:28:21.700 --> 00:28:24.470
is to know your inner obstacles.

00:28:24.470 --> 00:28:28.230
As Socrates said, know thyself.

00:28:28.230 --> 00:28:30.970
And that involves knowing
what's in the way of you

00:28:30.970 --> 00:28:33.490
being happier.

00:28:33.490 --> 00:28:36.116
Now I have a very--
I'm a psychotherapist,

00:28:36.116 --> 00:28:40.280
and I'm very good at pinpointing
for people their biggest

00:28:40.280 --> 00:28:44.032
obstacle in the way
of them being happier.

00:28:44.032 --> 00:28:45.470
And I'll show you how I do this.

00:28:45.470 --> 00:28:51.370
What I need is a volunteer
willing to come up and work

00:28:51.370 --> 00:28:52.690
with me.

00:28:52.690 --> 00:28:54.710
Raise your hand if you're
willing to volunteer.

00:28:54.710 --> 00:28:55.270
OK, great.

00:28:55.270 --> 00:28:58.290
Hold on just one second.

00:28:58.290 --> 00:29:00.720
I think something
is very interesting,

00:29:00.720 --> 00:29:05.480
and that is about a minute
ago, everybody in this room

00:29:05.480 --> 00:29:07.600
was a red pill taker.

00:29:07.600 --> 00:29:09.060
And then when I
say, would you like

00:29:09.060 --> 00:29:12.480
to take a red pill now and
know the truth of yourself

00:29:12.480 --> 00:29:16.630
as something that's in the
way have you being happier,

00:29:16.630 --> 00:29:19.270
there was only one
red pill taker.

00:29:19.270 --> 00:29:21.830
Isn't that interesting?

00:29:21.830 --> 00:29:24.190
You may not be as
dedicated to the red pill

00:29:24.190 --> 00:29:27.790
as you think because
when I asked, would you

00:29:27.790 --> 00:29:31.850
like to face a small amount
of potential embarrassment

00:29:31.850 --> 00:29:38.490
to know a valuable truth about
yourself, 98% of you said,

00:29:38.490 --> 00:29:39.240
yeah, but not now.

00:29:42.180 --> 00:29:45.240
So one obstacle that you
might have to being happier

00:29:45.240 --> 00:29:48.860
is that you have an ability
to say some story in your head

00:29:48.860 --> 00:29:54.280
as to why now is not a good
time to take a red pill.

00:29:54.280 --> 00:29:56.790
And that gets in the
way of us being happier.

00:29:56.790 --> 00:30:00.410
So just think back, what
did you say to yourself

00:30:00.410 --> 00:30:02.140
so that you didn't
have to come up here?

00:30:02.140 --> 00:30:05.435
This gentleman here
didn't have the same story

00:30:05.435 --> 00:30:07.285
or excuse that you did.

00:30:07.285 --> 00:30:11.342
And since he didn't,
he gets a free book.

00:30:11.342 --> 00:30:12.967
Let's give them a
hand for being brave.

00:30:12.967 --> 00:30:18.330
[APPLAUSE]

00:30:18.330 --> 00:30:20.830
JONATHAN ROBINSON:
Really, now I'm

00:30:20.830 --> 00:30:23.170
an easily fearful
person as well.

00:30:23.170 --> 00:30:24.890
I don't like being
embarrassed, but I

00:30:24.890 --> 00:30:27.240
am aware of the story in my
head that I always come up

00:30:27.240 --> 00:30:30.330
with for why now is not the
time to take the red pill.

00:30:30.330 --> 00:30:32.060
And sometimes--
not all the time--

00:30:32.060 --> 00:30:34.924
but sometimes, I
transcend that story.

00:30:34.924 --> 00:30:36.840
But first you have to
know what that story is,

00:30:36.840 --> 00:30:41.530
and you have to know that we're
always given an opportunity

00:30:41.530 --> 00:30:43.160
to take the red
pill or a blue pill.

00:30:43.160 --> 00:30:44.850
It's not one choice you make.

00:30:44.850 --> 00:30:49.230
It's a choice you
make 100 times a day.

00:30:49.230 --> 00:30:51.660
Whether or not to say
hello to the person,

00:30:51.660 --> 00:30:53.720
whether or not to say what
you're really thinking

00:30:53.720 --> 00:30:59.260
about them, whether or
not to say what you want.

00:30:59.260 --> 00:31:01.500
Those are little
red pill moments.

00:31:01.500 --> 00:31:04.080
And the more that
you take it, the more

00:31:04.080 --> 00:31:05.740
expanded your life
is likely to be.

00:31:08.360 --> 00:31:13.580
An eighth key for being happy
is to master the meaning

00:31:13.580 --> 00:31:15.277
that your mind creates.

00:31:15.277 --> 00:31:17.110
I mentioned before that
our minds are always

00:31:17.110 --> 00:31:22.080
creating a sense of
Velcro for negativity,

00:31:22.080 --> 00:31:25.714
and we want to make
it more like Teflon.

00:31:25.714 --> 00:31:27.380
How do you do that
in the midst of life?

00:31:27.380 --> 00:31:30.340
You get in a car accident, you
think, oh, this is horrible.

00:31:30.340 --> 00:31:32.650
Well, we need to be
able in that moment

00:31:32.650 --> 00:31:35.460
to change the meaning
we create for things

00:31:35.460 --> 00:31:38.362
so that we don't feel bad
for a long period of time.

00:31:38.362 --> 00:31:41.710
I'm reminded of a
story-- a businessman who

00:31:41.710 --> 00:31:46.300
once came to counseling for
me, he shared this story.

00:31:46.300 --> 00:31:48.520
And he was kind of an
arrogant, rich guy,

00:31:48.520 --> 00:31:50.700
and he said he was in
Thailand traveling.

00:31:50.700 --> 00:31:54.095
He went up to a monk
and he said to the monk,

00:31:54.095 --> 00:31:57.030
well, if you're so
wise, why don't you

00:31:57.030 --> 00:32:00.210
teach me a lesson
about Heaven and Hell?

00:32:00.210 --> 00:32:02.680
So this monk looks
up at him and says,

00:32:02.680 --> 00:32:05.050
teach you about Heaven and Hell?

00:32:05.050 --> 00:32:07.380
I couldn't teach you anything.

00:32:07.380 --> 00:32:09.410
You are like an arrogant man.

00:32:09.410 --> 00:32:11.580
You don't have a caring
bone in your body.

00:32:11.580 --> 00:32:12.600
You even smell bad.

00:32:12.600 --> 00:32:14.930
You probably eat meat.

00:32:14.930 --> 00:32:16.770
You just don't care
about anything.

00:32:16.770 --> 00:32:20.460
Just get out of my sight
and stop wasting my time.

00:32:20.460 --> 00:32:21.920
Well, the man gets
red in the face.

00:32:21.920 --> 00:32:22.950
He shakes with rage.

00:32:22.950 --> 00:32:25.820
He gets ready to punch
this monk in the face.

00:32:25.820 --> 00:32:27.810
And an instant before
he throws the punch,

00:32:27.810 --> 00:32:30.070
the monk says, that's Hell.

00:32:34.210 --> 00:32:36.300
Well, the man was
just overwhelmed

00:32:36.300 --> 00:32:39.410
that this monk risking
beaten up to teach him

00:32:39.410 --> 00:32:41.330
this lesson about Hell.

00:32:41.330 --> 00:32:44.440
He unclinched his fist, and
then he bowed to the monk.

00:32:44.440 --> 00:32:46.600
And the monk said,
and that's Heaven.

00:32:49.420 --> 00:32:52.040
What I like about that
story is that we're always

00:32:52.040 --> 00:32:54.160
creating our own moments
of Heaven and Hell

00:32:54.160 --> 00:32:55.580
by how we interpret things.

00:32:55.580 --> 00:32:57.440
He interpreted the
first words-- I'm

00:32:57.440 --> 00:33:00.950
be insulted for no good reason--
created a moment of Hell.

00:33:00.950 --> 00:33:02.500
He took the same
words a moment later

00:33:02.500 --> 00:33:04.916
and said that this person just
taught me a valuable lesson

00:33:04.916 --> 00:33:07.640
and created a
moment of gratitude.

00:33:07.640 --> 00:33:09.300
So how to do this
in a simple way?

00:33:09.300 --> 00:33:11.160
Well, there's one
question I use,

00:33:11.160 --> 00:33:16.450
and the question is what
could be good about this?

00:33:16.450 --> 00:33:18.220
What could potentially
be good about this?

00:33:18.220 --> 00:33:20.095
I mean, taking on
something big, like, again,

00:33:20.095 --> 00:33:21.379
to a fender bender.

00:33:21.379 --> 00:33:23.670
You don't think what could
be good about this normally,

00:33:23.670 --> 00:33:25.640
but hey, maybe I'll
meet this person.

00:33:25.640 --> 00:33:31.400
Maybe I was destined-- I met
my wife in a fender bender.

00:33:31.400 --> 00:33:34.930
That was useful.

00:33:34.930 --> 00:33:39.640
You could see focus
on, well, I might

00:33:39.640 --> 00:33:41.369
have been in a worse
accident later.

00:33:41.369 --> 00:33:42.660
I might have been killed later.

00:33:42.660 --> 00:33:45.550
Now I'm not going to because
I'm in a little fender bender.

00:33:45.550 --> 00:33:47.370
Or who knows what
you might think of.

00:33:47.370 --> 00:33:51.950
Maybe this will help me to
become a more careful driver.

00:33:51.950 --> 00:33:54.820
Whatever it is, we're
always making up the future.

00:33:54.820 --> 00:33:56.660
We don't know.

00:33:56.660 --> 00:33:58.929
You might as well make
it up so it's empowering,

00:33:58.929 --> 00:34:00.970
and a simple question like
that can help do that.

00:34:04.940 --> 00:34:08.880
This is me doing magic
for Syrian refugees

00:34:08.880 --> 00:34:10.949
a couple months ago.

00:34:10.949 --> 00:34:14.770
These are kids who
have lost parents,

00:34:14.770 --> 00:34:18.170
lost limbs, and
certainly lost a country.

00:34:18.170 --> 00:34:23.110
But in a moment of play and
humor, everybody is smiles.

00:34:23.110 --> 00:34:25.790
That's a power of
play and humor.

00:34:25.790 --> 00:34:26.870
And that's a skill.

00:34:26.870 --> 00:34:28.286
It's not a skill
we have to learn.

00:34:28.286 --> 00:34:30.550
Every three-year-old is playful.

00:34:30.550 --> 00:34:32.489
Average four-year-old
laughs 100 times a day.

00:34:32.489 --> 00:34:35.840
The average 12-year-old, twice.

00:34:35.840 --> 00:34:38.719
So being able to
enjoy play and humor.

00:34:38.719 --> 00:34:41.400
And we don't even
play tennis as adults.

00:34:41.400 --> 00:34:44.090
We compete at tennis.

00:34:44.090 --> 00:34:46.070
We compete at everything.

00:34:46.070 --> 00:34:50.610
But play and humor is a tonic
that makes all of life better.

00:34:50.610 --> 00:34:55.139
And to create an analogy that
might help you remember this,

00:34:55.139 --> 00:34:57.680
I'm going to do one
last magic trick.

00:34:57.680 --> 00:35:00.410
Could you throw this to any
random person in the audience?

00:35:00.410 --> 00:35:03.070
Just to-- oh, great.

00:35:03.070 --> 00:35:03.570
Yeah.

00:35:09.050 --> 00:35:11.000
OK, well, what I
want you to do is

00:35:11.000 --> 00:35:14.020
I want you to think of a
number between 1 and 1,000.

00:35:14.020 --> 00:35:15.760
Don't tell me what it is.

00:35:15.760 --> 00:35:18.040
And I'm going to write down
what you're going to say.

00:35:18.040 --> 00:35:19.082
OK?

00:35:19.082 --> 00:35:20.540
Now this really is
a random person.

00:35:20.540 --> 00:35:22.030
I want you to know that.

00:35:22.030 --> 00:35:23.255
I think I got it.

00:35:29.655 --> 00:35:30.155
OK.

00:35:32.860 --> 00:35:37.025
I'm always a little nervous
when it comes to this.

00:35:37.025 --> 00:35:39.650
I'm want you to speak up really
loud so everybody can hear you.

00:35:39.650 --> 00:35:40.983
I'm going to ask you a question.

00:35:40.983 --> 00:35:43.010
Is the number 237?

00:35:43.010 --> 00:35:43.899
Yes or no.

00:35:43.899 --> 00:35:44.440
AUDIENCE: No.

00:35:44.440 --> 00:35:47.810
JONATHAN ROBINSON: I wrote
down what he was going to say.

00:35:47.810 --> 00:35:50.220
Pretty good, huh?

00:35:50.220 --> 00:35:53.150
You are not impressed evidently.

00:35:53.150 --> 00:35:54.910
I can't tell you how
I do that secret,

00:35:54.910 --> 00:35:58.730
but what I can tell you
is it does have a point,

00:35:58.730 --> 00:36:01.370
and the point is I
try to set up life

00:36:01.370 --> 00:36:04.240
so I have a very good
chance of succeeding.

00:36:04.240 --> 00:36:07.180
When you bring play and
humor into your life,

00:36:07.180 --> 00:36:10.210
you have a very good
chance of succeeding

00:36:10.210 --> 00:36:12.420
at the game of happiness.

00:36:12.420 --> 00:36:14.500
So that's something you
might want to invest in.

00:36:14.500 --> 00:36:17.790
And last but not
least, tenth key

00:36:17.790 --> 00:36:20.480
before we go into the future
is if you want to be happy,

00:36:20.480 --> 00:36:23.230
you want to learn how
to dive into the now.

00:36:26.510 --> 00:36:29.800
Being here now is the
greatest key to happiness.

00:36:29.800 --> 00:36:32.050
And most people think that
they're already in the now,

00:36:32.050 --> 00:36:35.140
but mostly we're thinking
of problems and plans

00:36:35.140 --> 00:36:37.620
and relationships in
our chatterbox mind,

00:36:37.620 --> 00:36:41.310
and we never learn
how to let go of that.

00:36:41.310 --> 00:36:46.430
So we need to learn how to let
go of that and be here now.

00:36:46.430 --> 00:36:49.770
And be here now.

00:36:49.770 --> 00:36:51.645
And be here now.

00:36:51.645 --> 00:36:53.270
Now you may be
wondering how many times

00:36:53.270 --> 00:36:54.186
I'm going to say that.

00:36:54.186 --> 00:36:56.040
That's part of being
here now, being

00:36:56.040 --> 00:36:57.990
with what your thoughts
are saying about now.

00:37:05.510 --> 00:37:09.610
Being OK with silence is an
important part of being here

00:37:09.610 --> 00:37:13.060
now, one that we're not
very good at in this age

00:37:13.060 --> 00:37:16.470
where we can always
have something going on.

00:37:16.470 --> 00:37:20.040
Learning how to relax
and, beyond the turmoil

00:37:20.040 --> 00:37:24.280
of our minds, finding the deeper
ocean where peace actually

00:37:24.280 --> 00:37:28.270
always is is part
of being here now.

00:37:28.270 --> 00:37:32.510
And that's a skill
that is learnable.

00:37:32.510 --> 00:37:35.210
Now we talked about
being happy in the now.

00:37:35.210 --> 00:37:38.030
I want to now take
you on a tour of what

00:37:38.030 --> 00:37:42.070
is likely to happen towards
happiness in the future.

00:37:42.070 --> 00:37:44.070
And one thing to know
is that the stakes

00:37:44.070 --> 00:37:47.410
are big because if
we do this wrong,

00:37:47.410 --> 00:37:51.380
we could end up like rats
pressing that bar in a cage,

00:37:51.380 --> 00:37:55.490
stimulating ourselves
to have instant pleasure

00:37:55.490 --> 00:37:58.620
while everything
else in life goes by.

00:37:58.620 --> 00:38:01.920
Rats will actually die
pressing a pleasure button that

00:38:01.920 --> 00:38:06.900
is stimulating the pleasure
center of their brain

00:38:06.900 --> 00:38:09.020
because it's so powerful.

00:38:09.020 --> 00:38:12.980
Well, it's not long before
we are able to do that,

00:38:12.980 --> 00:38:15.560
and we want to make sure
that we don't sacrifice

00:38:15.560 --> 00:38:22.130
all the depth of life for
just instinct gratification.

00:38:22.130 --> 00:38:24.760
And there's certainly
billions if not trillions

00:38:24.760 --> 00:38:27.120
of dollars at stake
for people who

00:38:27.120 --> 00:38:29.880
learn how to help
people feel happy

00:38:29.880 --> 00:38:33.460
since that is what
we're ultimately after.

00:38:33.460 --> 00:38:36.240
Now there's five new
technologies or approaches

00:38:36.240 --> 00:38:38.790
to finding happiness I
want to briefly touch upon,

00:38:38.790 --> 00:38:40.300
and one of them--
the first one--

00:38:40.300 --> 00:38:44.610
is what I call sensory
and reality simulators.

00:38:44.610 --> 00:38:47.230
And these are already
happening to some extent.

00:38:47.230 --> 00:38:49.760
The Oculus Rift VR.

00:38:49.760 --> 00:38:53.030
Soon there's going to be
full body suits that people

00:38:53.030 --> 00:38:55.180
can wear for virtual reality.

00:38:55.180 --> 00:38:58.700
There's other things
like video games.

00:38:58.700 --> 00:39:01.630
Young people spend a huge
portion of their lives

00:39:01.630 --> 00:39:03.800
watching video games now.

00:39:03.800 --> 00:39:05.210
Is that a good thing?

00:39:05.210 --> 00:39:06.790
I don't know.

00:39:06.790 --> 00:39:08.540
We're doing an
experiment on humanity

00:39:08.540 --> 00:39:11.490
though in which a
large part of humanity

00:39:11.490 --> 00:39:15.280
is spending most of their free
time either watching TV, being

00:39:15.280 --> 00:39:17.330
on the internet, or
doing video games.

00:39:17.330 --> 00:39:20.790
And these will get much, much
better in the next few years,

00:39:20.790 --> 00:39:23.500
Much more addictive.

00:39:23.500 --> 00:39:26.374
And if you've ever read the
book "Reality Is Broken,"

00:39:26.374 --> 00:39:28.040
I think there's good
sides and bad sides

00:39:28.040 --> 00:39:29.760
to be made to this argument.

00:39:29.760 --> 00:39:31.680
But it will be
happening, and it will

00:39:31.680 --> 00:39:33.950
impact how people
find happiness.

00:39:33.950 --> 00:39:37.750
A second key-- this is even
a little bit more scary.

00:39:37.750 --> 00:39:40.130
These are what I
call brain enhancers.

00:39:40.130 --> 00:39:43.770
These are things like Direct
Brain Stimulation, or DBS.

00:39:43.770 --> 00:39:44.830
